\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 Summon.  Adjustment Powers work the same whether they\rquote re used on the \i\f2 eff ects \i0\f0 of a power or on the \i\f2 creator\par
\pard or originator \i0\f0 of the power. For example, a character could use Suppress Summon on a Summoned\par
demon, or on the wizard who cast the Summon spell; either attack could banish the demon if the\par
Suppress eff ect roll is high enough.\par
