\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 Some Powers and Characteristics are bought incrementally, at costs greater than 1 Character Point per increment.\fs20\par
\pard\fs19 In this case, a character using an Adjustment Power to reduce (or increase) that Power or Characteristic must remove (or add) enough Character Points to remove (or add) an entire increment of the Characteristic or Power\par
\emdash  removing (or adding) less than the number of Character Points required to buy 1 point of the\par
Characteristic (or one increment of the Power) has no eff ect.  If a Power is not bought in increments (for example, Desolidifi cation, which costs a fl at 40 Character Points), a character using a Drain or Transfer to reduce that Power or Characteristic must remove enough Character Points to remove the entire Power (including Adders and Advantages).\fs20\par
\fs19\tab\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 If you want to do some additional work, you can apportion the Character Points returned over time.\par
\pard Th is can be especially important when the return rate has been lengthened. For example, if the Character\par
Points from a Drain were bought to return at the rate of 5 Character Points per 5 hours, the GM could rule\par
that they return at the rate of 1 point per hour. Similarly, for shorter time intervals, the GM could allow\par
the points to return 12 Segments aft er the initial eff ect (rather than at the end of Segment 12). Th ese\par
variations increase the fl exibility of the Adjustment Powers at the expense of extra bookkeeping. Th ey\rquote re\par
not recommended for new GMs or when many characters are using Adjustment Powers.\fs20\par
\fs19\tab\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 When a character buys an Adjustment Power through a Multipower or Variable Power Pool, if\par
\pard he switches the Framework to another Power the boosted (or reduced) Characteristic or Power fades at\par
the standard rate (or whatever rate the character has paid for with the \i\f2 Delayed Return Rate \i0\f0 Advantage). It\par
does not dissipate immediately (but see below regarding improving a Power Framework slot).\par
\tab\tab Status: \b Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 If a character uses an Adjustment Power such as Aid to boost or increase a Power Framework,\par
\pard both the base \ldblquote pool\rdblquote  of points and the individual  slot or Power must be Adjusted. An Adjustment\par
Power that works on more than one Power of a given special eff ect simultaneously (see below) can\par
aff ect both the Framework\rquote s pool of points and one or more of its slots or powers at once; otherwise\par
they have to be Adjusted one at a time. Th e points in an individual Multipower slot or Variable Power\par
Pool power cannot exceed the points in the pool, regardless of the total rolled on the Adjustment\par
Power dice\par
\tab\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 If an Adjustment Power is used to Drain or remove points from either the base cost or any slot\par
\pard in an Elemental Control, \i\f2 all slots and the base cost are equally aff ected. \i0\f0 Th is is one of the prices the\par
character pays for the point savings of an EC \emdash  the EC powers are so closely related that to Drain or\par
Transfer points from one of them is to do it to all of them. Th is occurs even if the Adjustment Power\par
is not bought to aff ect all the powers of a given special eff ect at once, or is bought only to aff ect a\par
single Power. Removing points from an Elemental Control this way essentially doubles the eff ectiveness of the\par
Adjustment Power. If an attacker Drains 15 Character Points from a slot in a character\rquote s EC, the EC\par
loses 15 Character Points from both the base cost \i\f2 and \i0\f0 from every slot, so the overall loss of power for\par
any given slot is 30 Character Points. (If the Adjustment Power is used against a slot that\rquote s built with a\par
Defense Power, halve the Adjustment Power\rquote s eff ect only against that slot; it has full eff ect on the base\par
cost and all other slots.) Th e converse is \i\f2 not \i0\f0 true: Adjustment Powers such as Aid which increase or improve an Elemental\par
Control\rquote s base cost or one of its slots must aff ect \i\f2 both \i0\f0 the base cost and the slot before there is any\par
gain or benefi t. Furthermore, the gain or benefi t is limited to the smaller of the two amounts added.\par
For example, if a character has Aid Energy Blast 4d6 and uses it to add 15 Character Points to an\par
Energy Blast 6d6 slot, the Aid has no eff ect until the base cost is also Aided. If the Aid result for the base\par
cost is 20 Character Points, the Energy Blast is only Aided by 15 Character Points \emdash  the smaller of the\par
two amounts.\par
\tab\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 If a character uses an Adjustment Power to boost, increase, or improve a slot or power in a\par
\pard Multipower or VPP, and the subject switches the Framework to another slot or power, the points\par
added to the previous slot or power instantly fade. When the character switches the Framework back\par
to the Power which was Adjusted, it\rquote s at its usual strength, not its Adjusted strength. On the other\par
hand, if a character uses Drain or similar Adjustment Powers to reduce or decrease a slot or power\par
in a Framework, the slot or Power regains the lost points at the standard rate for the power, regardless\par
of whether the victim switches the Framework to another slot or power.\par
\tab\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\b0\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720 If a character uses an Adjustment Power toboost, increase, or improve a VPP, he has to improve\par
\pard both the Pool and the Control Cost. For every 2points added to the Pool, he must add 1 to the\par
Control Cost so that he maintains the proper ratio between them. If the points added by the Adjustment\par
Power aren\rquote t evenly divisible this way, any overage has no eff ect. For example, if a character uses Aid to add\par
5 points of eff ect to a VPP, the fi rst 2 points go to the Pool, and the third point goes to the Control Cost.\par
Since the remaining 2 points aren\rquote t enough to apply 2-and-1 in this fashion, they have no eff ect. However,\par
the remainder fades at the usual rate, and can be added to by another use of the Adjustment Power\par
later on, potentially taking eff ect\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 If a character uses Adjustment Powers such as Drain to reduce or decrease a Power Framework,\par
\pard he must reduce the individual slots rather than the base pool of points. (so this seems to be saying you can't drain the framework pool of a framework except for an EC which has the rules above)\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 Adjustment Powers never aff ect the point of a character\rquote s \ldblquote negative BODY.\rdblquote  If a character normally\par
\pard has 10 BODY, then he dies at -10 BODY, even if Aided to 15 BODY or Drained to 5 BODY. A\par
character reduced to negative his BODY solely due to an Adjustment Power dies\par
\tab Status: \b HCS does this incorrectly\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 If a character is in the negative BODY range due to a wound, and an Adjustment Power takes\par
\pard him to positive BODY, he stops Post-Segment 12 bleeding from the wound as long as the Adjustment\par
Power keeps his BODY score positive. When the fading of the Adjustment Power returns him to\par
negative BODY, he starts bleeding again in Post-Segment 12.\par
\tab Status: \b Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 If a character is in the negative BODY range due to a wound, and an Adjustment Power adds\par
\pard to that eff ect, he keeps bleeding from the wound on Post-Segment 12 and eventually dies (or dies\par
immediately if the Adjustment Power takes him to negative his starting BODY).\fs20\par
\fs19\tab Status: \b Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Attack Powers: \f0 If a character boosts or improves an Attack Power such as Energy Blast or HKA\par
\pard with Aid or a similar Adjustment Power, the extra damage counts as \ldblquote base damage\rdblquote  for purposes of\par
determining how much damage the character can add with STR, movement, Combat Skill Levels, and\par
the like.\par
