\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\fs19 Area Of Effect, Explosion: \f0 If an Adjustment Power (other than Transfer; see page 236) has this Advantage,\par
\pard it aff ects everyone in the area equally, up to its maximum aff ect per individual. For example,\par
if an Aid STR, Area Of Eff ect (Radius) can add a maximum of 12 Character Points, everyone in that\par
radius can gain up to 12 Characters Points\rquote  worth of STR. If an Adjustment Power does not work this\par
way \emdash  if it has to divide its eff ect equally between everyone in the aff ected Area \emdash  it may take a -\'be\par
Limitation, \i\f2 Divided Eff ect.\i0\f0\fs20\par
