\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\fs19 Can Apply (Remove) Adders (+1): \f0 A character can use an Adjustment Power with this Advantage to\par
\pard apply Adders to a Power which that Power does not already have, or can enhance an existing Adder\par
if appropriate. Th e character chooses what Adders to apply when he uses the Adjustment Power; the\par
Adder applied can vary from use to use. An alternate version, \i\f2 Can Remove Adders, \i0\f0 is\par
appropriate for Adjustment Powers such as Drain. It allows the Power to remove Adders a target\par
Power possesses. Th e Adders are removed fi rst,before the base Power itself is Adjusted.\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Cumulative: \f0 Characters should not apply Cumulative to Adjustment Powers that increase a Power\par
\pard or Characteristic (such as Aid or Absorption), since they have their own rules for how many\par
Character Points they can add to a particular Characteristic or Power and how and at what\par
rate they\rquote re added. Th ey can apply Cumulative to Adjustment Powers that decrease a Power or\par
Characteristic (such as Suppress). \par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Delayed Return Rate (+\'bc or greater)\fs20\par
\pard\fs19\tab Status: \b Implemented\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\fs19 Variable Effect (+\'bc to +2): \f0 To apply an Adjustment Power to any Characteristic or Power within\par
\pard a related group of special eff ects, \i\f2 one Power at a time, \i0\f0 is a +\'bc Power Advantage. Th us, a character\par
could have, for example, a Drain that works against any one fi re-based Power. For a +\'bd Advantage, a character can apply an adjustment Power to any two Characteristics or Powers with related special eff ects simultaneously.\par
For a +1 Advantage, a character can apply an Adjustment Power to any four Characteristics or Powers with related special eff ects simultaneously.For a +2 Advantage, a character can apply an Adjustment Power to \i\f2 all \i0\f0 Characteristics and\par
Powers with related special eff ects simultaneously(regardless of how many there are).\fs20\par
\fs19\tab Status: \b Implemented.  However, " \i\f2 all \i0\f0 Characteristics and\par
Powers with related special eff ects simultaneously" HCS should not prompt you to select the items\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0 Instead of defi ning a Variable Eff ect power as aff ecting a pure special eff ect, a character can defi ne\par
\pard it as working against any similarly related grouping of Characteristics and/or Powers. Examples include\par
\ldblquote four defi ned Characteristics at once\rdblquote  (+1), \ldblquote any Characteristic that\rquote s currently below starting value,\par
one at a time\rdblquote  (+\'bc), or \ldblquote any Sense-Aff ecting Power, one at a time\rdblquote  (+\'bc).\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Variable Effect \emdash  Multiple Special Effects: \f0 At the GM\rquote s option, a character who\rquote s bought Variable\par
\pard Eff ect at the +\'bd or greater level can buy a separate Advantage, \i\f2 Multiple Special Eff ects, \i0\f0 to increase the\par
number of \i\f2 special eff ects \i0\f0 he can aff ect. For a +\'bc Advantage, an Adjustment Power with Variable\par
Eff ect can aff ect either of two special eff ects, but only one special eff ect at a time. For a +\'bd Advantage,\par
an Adjustment Power with Variable Eff ect can aff ect the defi ned number of powers in two special\par
eff ects simultaneously. For a +1 Advantage, it can aff ect the defi ned number of powers in four special\par
eff ects simultaneously. For a +2 Advantage, it can aff ect the defi ned number of powers in all special\par
eff ects simultaneously.\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implmented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Charges: \f0 With the GM\rquote s permission, a character can use an Adjustment Power just to aff ect a target\par
\pard power\rquote s Charges. Divide the Active Points in the power by the number of Charges it has. Using the\par
resulting \ldblquote point total\rdblquote  for each Charge, apply the Adjustment Power as per normal.\par
If a power has Continuing Charges, and an Adjustment Power is applied to it, the Adjustment Power typically aff ects the entire power (\i\f2 i.e., \i0\f0 all Charges, whether in use or not), not just the Charge currently in eff ect. However, at the GM\rquote s option, a\par
character could declare that he wants to Adjust only the Charge(s) in eff ect at a particular time (or the\par
GM may restrict him to doing so).\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Gradual Effect: \f0 If a character applies the \i\f2 Gradual Eff ect \i0\f0 Limitation to a negative Adjustment Power,\par
\pard such as Drain or Transfer, the target doesn\rquote t start regaining lost points until all increments of eff ect\par
have accrued. Once the last increment accrues, he starts regaining lost points at the specifi ed rate\par
for the power. Th e same is \i\f2 not \i0\f0 true of Adjustment Powers that boost or improve game elements, such\par
as Aid; their eff ects fade at the standard rate regardless of the Gradual Eff ect increment. If the GM\par
feels any of this might be abusive or pose game\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Increased Return Rate (-\'bc or more): \f0 For some powers, a character may want to increase the rate at\par
\pard which the Character Points added or removed by an Adjustment Power fade or return.\par
If an Adjustment Power doesn\rquote t have the \i\f2 Delayed Return Rate \i0\f0 Advantage, then every doubling\par
of the amount of points that fade/return per time increment is a -\'bc Limitation, \i\f2 Increased\par
Fade(Return) Rate: \i0\f0 -\'bc if the points fade/return at 10 per time increment; -\'bd if the points fade/return\par
at the rate of 20 per time increment; and so on (assuming the GM allows any further increase in\par
the rate of fade/return). If all the points fade/return immediately when 1 Turn or some lesser increment\par
of time passes, that\rquote s worth a fl at -\'bd (the GM may reduce this to -\'bc if the Adjustment Power typically\par
adds/removes 10 or fewer Character Points). If an Adjustment Power has the \i\f2 Delayed\par
Return Rate \i0\f0 Advantage, the Limitation described above simply reduces the value of the Advantage,\par
but the Advantage has a minimum value of +\'bc. Th e GM may alter the value of the Advantage as he sees\par
fi t to preserve game balance.\tab\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Limited Special Effect (-\'bc or more): \f0 If a character buys an Adjustment Power to aff ect a specifi c\par
\pard Power (Aid Energy Blast, Drain Telekinesis), it takes this Limitation if it can only aff ect that Power\par
when the Power has a particular special eff ect. Examples include Aid Energy Blast, Fire Special\par
Eff ect Only (-\'bd), or Drain Telekinesis, Mentalism Special Eff ect Only (-\'bd). Th e value of the Limitation\par
depends upon how common the special eff ect is; a Very Common special eff ect would be worth\par
-\'bc, a Common special eff ect -\'bd, and an Uncommon special eff ect -1.\par
\tab Status; \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 One Use At A Time (-\'bd): \f0 If a character cannot use an Adjustment Power on a target a subsequent time until\par
\pard the fi rst use fades entirely, it takes this Limitation.\par
\tab Satus: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Only Restores To Starting Values (-\'bd): \f0 Some Adjustment Powers can raise Characteristics and Powers\par
\pard far above their starting levels. If an Adjustment Power can only restore lost Characteristics and\par
Powers (but not raise them above starting values), it\rquote s bought with a -\'bd Limitation. Characters cannot\par
take this Limitation for Healing (which by defi nition nition only restores Characteristics and Powers to\par
their starting levels) or for Adjustment Powers with a Variable Eff ect defi ned as aff ecting \ldblquote Characteristics\par
and Powers below starting value.\rdblquote\par
\tab Status: \b Not Implemented\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\b0\f1 Self Only (-\'bd): \f0 An Adjustment Power that can af ect others, such as Aid, may take this Limitation\par
\pard if the character who buys it can only use it on himself. A similar Limitation is \i\f2 Others Only\par
\i0\f0 (-\'bd), meaning the character who buys the Power can never use it on himself.\par
